{
  "texts": [
    "Initialization improvementLoRA usually initializes its parameter matrices A and B using Gaussian noise and zeros respectively.",
    "There are two simple schemes: Init[A], which sets matrix B to zero and randomly initializes matrix A, and Init[B], which does the reverse.",
    "Literature [36] compares these two schemes and concludes that Init[A] is better through theoretical analysis.",
    "It reveals that Init[A] allows using a larger learning rate without causing instability, making the learning process more efficient.",
    "However, even with Init[A], this random initialization method still results in small initial gradients, leading to slower convergence."
  ]
}